$ C: datatype wchar_t

{ Macros #wchar_t-macros

  Some macros can be used to describe the `wchar_t` type.

  Including `<wchar.h>` makes the macro `WCHAR_MAX` available.

  At least → development/languages/C-C-plus-plus/GCC/index[gcc] also defines some `__WCHAR*` macros:

  gh|about-c|/datatypes/wchar_t/macros.c||

  This program might print something like
code {
WCHAR_MAX:             0x7fffffff
__SIZEOF_WCHAR_T__:    4
__WCHAR_MAX__:         0x7fffffff
__WCHAR_MIN__:         (-0x7fffffff - 1)
__WCHAR_UNSIGNED__:    __WCHAR_UNSIGNED__
__WCHAR_TYPE__:        int
code }

}

sa:

  The → development/languages/C-C-plus-plus/GCC/options/f/short/wchar[`-fshort-wchar`] GNU compiler option.

  → development/languages/C-C-plus-plus/C/language/datatypes[Datatypes]
